The taxi industry is also rejecting the R1-billion relief fund announced by Transport Minister Fikile Mbalula last week. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - KZN taxi owners and drivers are adamant that on Monday, they’ll load at full capacity - or shut down. According to the current COVID-19 regulations, minibus taxis are only allowed to load passengers to 70-percent capacity. READ: Taxi industry meeting postponed again The taxi industry’s also rejecting the R1-billion relief fund announced by Transport Minister Fikile Mbalula last week.